1. Introduction

  1. In the NBA, each team can play a maximum number of five players on the court. If a team breaks this main rule, they will lose possession of the ball.(MasterClass ,2022) The 5 positions in basketball are shooting guard, point guard, power forward, small forward, and center.In order to win the game, a team must score more field goals than the other team. A field goal refers to any basket a player scores during game play. Field goals can be worth two or three points.(Adams,2021)

  2. It is undeniable that if you have more budget to pay players in your team, your team would have better players. It leads to more win. (Chicago Bulls placed 27th out of 30 based on win-loss record in 18-19 season. The budget for next season is $118 million which ranked 26th out of 30 teams in NBA. The team with the highest payroll budget is Porland with $148 million, while the best performing team was Milwaukee Bucks with $131 million.) However, sometimes less payroll team could do better performance over whole season. That is why general manager is important to recruit cost-effective players.

  3. As a recruiting expert of Chicago Bulls, I am charged of finding the best find starting players in each position. Of course, The budget is limited. I will find the best cost-effective starting players using my data analysis skill.Considering diverse variables, he standard would be different depends on general manager of team, The budget for 5 starting player will not exceed 40% of next season budget which is 47.2 million.

  4. NBA is the one of the most popular league in the world at the moment. The NBA makes money from many different sources primarily through television, merchandising, sponsorships, and tickets. That is why they can spend lots of money on players. However, losing fan due to their performance impacts their revenue in many different ways. In fact, Recruiting great players within budget and win the games is the best way to keep their profits.(Wertheim,2022)

D) Justification for decision made about data modelling

Upgrading PTS variable depends on how many matches player played and Age

data_newpoints<- data %>% mutate(Points = PTS+(5*G) -(10*Age))

###Relationship Games and new points
ggplot(data_newpoints, aes(x=G, y=Points))+
  geom_point()

ggplot(data_newpoints, aes(x=Age, y=Points))+
  geom_point()

For Game variable, it is very important variable because it shows How many matches the players play in the season. It can tell how durable they are and attitude to prepare each game. Therefore, we decide to give 5 extra point per one game they played. The relation between Games and points become clearer giving them extra 5 points per game. It is way more positive. How many games they have played in a season cannot be ignored for athlete.

For Age variable, even though two players got same point overall season, potentially, younger player have more chance to upgrade or develope their performance. Therefore, if two players got same points and salary, picking younger players will be more helpful to team in the future. Therefore, age also should be considered, Age*10 will be deducted from points so older player will get less points if the performance was same with younger player.

For model1, The PTS variable can be a great standard of selecting players. It represent performance of each players well. It is highly correlated with almost every statistics except for “G”, “GS”, and “TOV”. The model 1 can be upgraded more to model2.

As we discussed before, Two variables (G, Age) which did not impact on points was well applied by multiplying their value and add or deduct to points. Therefore, we have two more standard to pick great 5players with points.

Model1 R-squared: 0.9978 Model2 R-squared: 0.9985

R-squared values range from 0 to 1 and are commonly stated as percentages from 0% to 100%. An R-squared of 100% means that all movements of a security (or another dependent variable) are completely explained by movements in the index(Fernando, 2022).

The R-squared proved that the new variable “Points” is very great to explain players’ performance. We will use “Points” variable to select best 5 players in 19-20 season.

6.Summary

The best 5 start players and salary 18-19 seasons are: Center -> Karl-Anthony Towns (7839435) Power forward -> Pascal Siakam (1544951) Point Guard -> D’Angelo Russell (7019698) Small Forward -> Jayson Tatum (6700800) Shooting Guard -> Donovan Mitchell (3111480)

The 5 players got paid 18-19 season 7839435+1544951+7019698+6700800+3111480 = $26,216,364(26.2m) in total. these players are the best cost-effectiveness players and will greatly help the team in many different ways!

Their pay increases are inevitable and must recruit them by raising their wages from 20 percent to up to 50 percent. They deserve it.

In this case, the total amount of money spent on 5 these players will be between 31.45m ~ 39.32m and it still does not exceed 40% of season budget in 19-20 season.

We expect the best performance with these fantastic 5 players next season.
